libserialport
------------------------------------------
libserialport is a minimal, cross-platform shared library written in C that is
intended to take care of the OS-specific details when writing software that
uses serial ports.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.7-1
  libserialport-devel-0.1.2-1bl1
  libserialport0-0.1.2-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.44-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sigrok.org/wiki/Libserialport

Canonical download:
  git://sigrok.org/libserialport

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libserialport-0.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libserialport-0.1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libserialport-0.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libserialport-0.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libserialport0-0.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libserialport-devel-0.1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libserialport)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libserialport.README
  /usr/share/doc/libserialport/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libserialport/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libserialport/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libserialport/README

(libserialport0)
  /usr/bin/cygserialport-0.dll

(libserialport-devel)
  /usr/include/libserialport.h
  /usr/lib/libserialport.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libserialport.pc

